5000|$|The {{formula for}} calculating the LNG {{transferred}} {{depends on the}} contractual sales conditions. These can relate to three types of sale contract as defined by Incoterms 2000: an FOB sale, a <b>CIF</b> <b>sale</b> or a DES sale.|$|E
50|$|The type of {{insurance}} contract {{depends on the}} Incoterm adopted by the parties in a sale contract. A <b>CIF</b> <b>sale</b> contract requires the seller to obtain insurance cover for the voyage. An FOB contract however places no obligation on the buyer or seller to obtain insurance, although it is prudent for the buyer to protect against potential losses. It {{is not uncommon for}} the buyer in a FOB contract to request the seller to arrange insurance on an understanding that they will reimburse the insurance costs incurred.|$|E

